# Current AWS region for production cluster: us-west-1
# If you want to move the production cluster from running in one region to another:
#   1) Comment out one block and uncomment the other block.
#   2) Stop all 'production' ec2 instances in the old region
#   3) Run the following command locally (install MongoDB first) to clear the node_monitor table:
#	       mongo c48.lighthouse.3.mongolayer.com:10048/graphistry-prod -u graphistry -p graphtheplanet --eval 'db.node_monitor.remove({})'
#   4) Start the appropriate ec2 instances in the new region.
#   5) Run Ansible to provision and/or deploy to the new instances
#   6) [Optional] change the DNS records on NameCheap to point labs.graphistry.com to the new IP
# Do NOT allow clusters to run in both regions simultaneously, or run Ansible with both AWS regions
# uncommented below.

